																			<div class="story first">
						<h3><a href="http://www.avimator.com/2007/02/21/6/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to About Avimator">About Avimator</a></h3>
						<p>Avimator is an easy-to-use, open source tool for creating and editing avatar animations for <a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/secondlife.com');"  href="http://secondlife.com" target="_blank" title="Second Life">Second Life</a>. It is a free alternative to Poser and Maya, and it runs on Windows, Mac OS X, and Linux. Download the latest version below. For a tutorial on how to create a simple avatar animation and upload it to Second Life, see the beginner&#8217;s guide in the download section.  Enjoy!</p>
<p>By: Vinay Pulim (Vince Invincible) </p>
						<div class="details">
							Posted at 2pm on 02/21/07 | <a href="http://www.avimator.com/2007/02/21/6/#comments" title="Comment on About Avimator">19 comments</a> | Filed Under: <a href="http://www.avimator.com/category/uncategorized/" title="View all posts in Uncategorized" rel="category tag">Uncategorized</a> <span class="read-on"><a href="http://www.avimator.com/2007/02/21/6/">read on</a></span>
						</div>
					</div>
														<div class="story">
						<h3><a href="http://www.avimator.com/2007/01/10/introducing-avimator/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to QAvimator">QAvimator</a></h3>
						<p>Development of Avimator has been put on hold for now. In the meantime, try  <a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/www.qavimator.org');"  href="http://www.qavimator.org" target="_blank" title="QAvimator site">QAvimator</a>.  It contains many enhancements to the original source code and has many useful features.</p>
